I came here on First Friday before and it was super loud and packed. I prefer coming here on the weekends for lunch. There's still noise but it's a little more family friendly. The pies range between $17 to $20. They also sell pies by the slices for cheese and pepperoni only.  For parking, there is metered street parking along Bethel Street or parking inside Marks Garage which is right across the street. They do not offer validation for parking within any of the parking garages.

Once a favorite spot of mine to enjoy a good pizza and beer, J.J. Dolans has become too uptight to have a good time and hang loose. Stories abound of customers being asked to leave when the are "too loud", "swear", or place their glasses on the tables "too loudly". Last time I checked, this establishment is still listed as a bar, so what gives? Yes, they still have one of the best shrimp scampi pizzas on the island, but the strict unwritten code of conduct seems to cater to the prim and proper type of clientele. Not my cup of tea.
